 classroom tool for courses on Spanish women writers, Spanish culture, and cross-cultural feminist studies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aFeminismzSpain. 0aSex rolezSpain. 0aWomenxEmploymentzSpain. 0aWomen's rightszSpain. 4aArea Studies : Hispanic Studies. 4aGender and Sexuality : Gender Studies. 4aGender and Sexuality : Women's Studies. 4aPhilosophy : Feminist Philosophy. 4aPolitics and Law : Politics. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Feminism & Feminist Theory.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781438473710?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438473710423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438473710/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles